author: Aric_Holbrook
body:
Hey apes,

**I know today for some of us was still a +7% day, and for others, it was an "uh oh I am freaking out" kinda day.** So I have been looking in the Mega-Thread and I stumbled upon a comment about a GME analysis! **I watched a few of this guy's videos and I have to say I am impressed. He is pretty well-spoken, so if you are feeling uneasy or confused go ahead and give this analysis a listen.**

[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BzmWAlSpmZE](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BzmWAlSpmZE)

Rember guys -uh apes excuse me- this is not like the last time.

1. **Look at the more gradual climb of the Stock, no really.** I know that may sound crazy, being up 1055 this week alone, but compared to last time it's a HUGGGGGGEEEE difference.
2. **We are still up $10\~ 7%, after a 107% drop today,** in comparison to last time you should be at least a little reaffirmed!
3. **Look at the options call to put ratio,** it is still extremely bullish, and with the massive, I MEAN MASSIVE 300c volume expiring this week-- SHEESH!
4. **Probably the most important, THIS IS NOT OUR FIRST TIME HERE????** I know you all know where this is going... We dropped like shit from ass cheeks and we bounced back, 1000s of shares were immediately bought? COME ON DO THEY KNOW WHO WE ARE, WHAT OUR COMMUNITY IS???

TL:DR- Just watch the video apes, it is insightful and helps put things in perspective. And remember APE strong, we can do this, we will finish what we started.

I am not a FA, We just like the stock man.

author: Camposaurus_Rex
body:
Inflation happens when the M2 expands (banks lending) and the money reaches the economy (M2 Velocity shows how easily money is exchanged between hands of business and consumers). I'm not sure I understand what the overturn of money means. However, when people pay down debt, money is destroyed in the process. The data has been showing people are paying down debt, which is likely why the M2 has remained relatively flat for the last few months.

If you have the time, I found this video to be super interesting and enlightening on the banks' role with the money supply. I also have a massive distaste for the central banks now.
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jkKwcXSbDK4&ab_channel=SIMAY2K

author: Hypoglybetic
body:
GME would not cause the system to collapse but it would expose how the system is manipulated.  [This video explains how](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=I0WXg5T3cBE) the system could collapse if the SEC were to enforce FTDs.  The concept is simple, someone sells shares they don't have, then they take that money out of the system (buys a lambo, 5th house).  Entities manipulate the system to kick the can down the road, and it is feared this could be a large percent of trades (between 7-35% according to the video).   

We have no idea how bad it is.  But if the theories are correct, and looking at 2008 and all the shit they do, I would not be surprised.

author: Flaky_Section
body:
I have something of a hot take on the “Reddit rebellion”. At first, I loved it. Then, I hated it. And then, I loved it again. Here’s the thing. Look at what they’re going after. Rocket mortgage, GME, even AMC/BB. These were all companies that were overshorted. The price was artificially held down by the high short percentage. They were undervalued in most cases because of that. Shorts got greedy, and got taught a lesson that they can no longer act with impunity. Now, clearly a lot of these have swung wildly to the upside, and will have to come down significantly to settle near fair value. But isn’t this the sign of a market functioning the way it should? Clearly, this shit has unnerved the broader market, or parts of it anyway, for stretches that has made this v painful at times to watch. But GME was a penny stock for a while this past year, while it still had billions in cash flow and a new console cycle coming. As long as these stocks settle closer to fair value, I actually am beginning to think that the positives outweighs the negatives over the longer term. 

Flying taxi SPACs, well, that’s a different story for a different time!!!

author: rmunoz1994
body:
**SOLID DD HERE!!!!**🚀

I figured out the **ENDGAME**.

We are blasting off to the moon. That was always the goal. But did you notice something about the word moon?

We can also type as so

`moon = Moon = M00N = M00IV`

Now we are left with digits and roman numerals. Now lets dig deeper. We will assume charitable values for the roman numeral since it's the freaking moon. M is the thousands in roman numerals. But we can be more charitable, because we all know that 1000 is the bare minimum. So I believe it instead reads as: 

`IVI`

`I & V & I`

Therefore, instead of limiting ourselves to the mere 1 thousands place with `M` we assume that the first three digits are 1,5, and 1. Coincidental that it is the number of original pokemon? You tell me, but this thread looks like a bunch of primeapes here. 0, 0  is self explanatory, but for the who ate too many crayons...we are now at 1,5,1,0, and 0. All that is left is the N.

`I V I 0 0 I V = 1 5 1 0 0 1 5`

Therefore, with solid and reliable DD that is totally not financial advice, I believe I have conclusively and single handedly proven that GME will hit ***$1,510,015*** by the end of the squeeze.
